# Library Management System â€“ Java OOP Project

##  Project Overview
The Library Management System is a Java-based console application created during the Coding Samurai Java Development Internship.  
It demonstrates the use of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts to manage library operations efficiently.

## Features
- View available and issued books
- Borrow books with availability check
- Return previously issued books
- Simple and intuitive menu system

## Technologies Used
- Java (Core Java)
- Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
- Arrays for data storage
- Scanner class for user input

##  OOP Concepts Applied
- Classes and objects
- Encapsulation
- Constructors
- Method abstraction

